      <![CDATA[
# Introduction

Welcome to **My Docs** — the documentation site for your project.

This template was built with [XMLUI](https://xmlui.org) and gives you a fully functional
documentation site out of the box. Edit the pages in `src/components/` to add your own content.

## What You Get

This docs template includes:

- **Sidebar navigation** with collapsible groups and icons
- **Table of contents** that auto-builds from headings on each page
- **Markdown support** for all your documentation content
- **Dark / light mode** toggle in the header
- **Responsive layout** that works on mobile and desktop

## How It's Structured

```
src/
├── Main.xmlui            ← app shell, navigation, routing
└── components/
    ├── DocPage.xmlui     ← content wrapper with TOC sidebar
    ├── Introduction.xmlui
    ├── QuickStart.xmlui
    ├── Installation.xmlui
    ├── Configuration.xmlui
    ├── CoreConcepts.xmlui
    ├── AdvancedUsage.xmlui
    ├── ApiOverview.xmlui
    ├── ApiEndpoints.xmlui
    └── Changelog.xmlui
```

Each page is an XMLUI component that wraps its content in `<DocPage>`.
The `DocPage` component renders the content alongside a Table of Contents sidebar.

## Getting Started

1. Edit the `<NavPanel>` in `src/Main.xmlui` to update the sidebar links.
2. Add or remove `<Page>` entries in the `<Pages>` block.
3. Create a corresponding `.xmlui` file in `src/components/` for each new page.
4. Replace the placeholder Markdown with your actual documentation.

Head over to the [Quick Start](/quick-start) guide to see the next steps.
      ]]>
    </Markdown>
  </DocPage>
</Component>
